🌍 Find-ISS
Track the real-time location of the International Space Station (ISS) on an interactive Google Map. This web app fetches live ISS coordinates and displays them with country details.

🚀 Features
✅ Live ISS Tracking – Fetch real-time latitude & longitude from the ISS API.
✅ Google Maps Integration – Visualize ISS location on a dynamic map.
✅ Country Detection – Converts coordinates into country names.
✅ Smart Zoom – Adjusts zoom level if ISS is over the ocean.
✅ Auto Refresh – Click a button to update the ISS position.
✅ Secure API Keys – Uses .env to keep keys safe.

🛠️ Technologies Used
Node.js & Express.js – Backend framework.
EJS – Templating engine.
Axios – Fetch external API data.
Google Maps API – Display map & markers.
dotenv – Secure API keys.
CSS & HTML – Styled frontend.
Render (Hosting) – Deploy the app online.

🔧 Installation & Setup
1️⃣ Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/your-username/Find-ISS.git
cd Find-ISS

2️⃣ Install dependencies
npm install

3️⃣ Set up environment variables
Create a .env file and add:
GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=your_api_key_here

4️⃣ Run the app
npm start

5️⃣ Open in browser
Visit http://localhost:3000/ to see the ISS tracking live!    

🌍 API References
Where The ISS At API – Provides real-time ISS location.
Google Maps API – Renders the map.
